=========================================
    PHONERAKSHAK FEATURE LIST & ROADMAP
=========================================

This document outlines the capabilities of the PhoneRakshak ecosystem (Server, Client APK, and Admin Dashboard) along with the pending roadmap items that need to be solved to reach ultimate completion.

-----------------------------------------
1. SERVER BACKEND FEATURES (Provided to Customer/Admin)
-----------------------------------------
- Instant Command Dispatch: Utilizes Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) to instantly push commands to offline/dozing devices using high-priority data payloads.
- Hybrid Fallback Reliability: Maintains a state machine (Queued -> Processing -> Executed). If FCM fails, HTTP Polling guarantees command delivery within a 15-second timeout window.
- Real-Time Device Tracking: Tracks and stores highly accurate device GPS locations, storing them dynamically for live map rendering.
- Intruder Logging: Processes and stores silent photos taken by the phone when an unauthorized user attempts to unlock the device.
- Ironclad Security: Implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication with a 7-day auto-refresh cycle and express-rate-limit to protect against brute force DDoS attacks.
- Real-Time Socket Connections: Streams live data to the Admin Dashboard (e.g., instant location pings, SIM change alerts) via Socket.io.

-----------------------------------------
2. CLIENT APK FEATURES (Installed on Target Device)
-----------------------------------------
- Stealth Operation: Operates silently in the background with AES256-GCM hardware encryption for all sensitive data (EncryptedSharedPreferences).
- Battery-Optimized Adaptive Polling: Rests at a 60-second polling interval but instantly revs up to 10 seconds when actively receiving commands.
- Offline SMS Fallback: Capable of receiving legacy SMS commands (e.g., LOCK<PIN>) to trigger actions even when mobile data is disabled.
- Silent Intruder Selfie: Automatically snaps a photo using the front camera when an incorrect PIN is entered on the lock screen.
- SIM Change Detection: Constantly monitors the SIM card fingerprint. If an unauthorized SIM is inserted, it instantly alerts the backend and sends an SMS to the emergency contact.
- 5-Minute Heartbeat: Automatically pings the server every 5 minutes to prove the device is online and active.
- Idempotent Command Execution: Strictly ensures that no remote command is ever executed twice, even across reboots.

-----------------------------------------
3. ADMIN DASHBOARD FEATURES (Web UI Control Center)
-----------------------------------------
- Glassmorphism UI: A premium, modern, and responsive interface designed to wow users.
- Live Map Tracking: Integrates Leaflet.js to plot recent GPS coordinates and device movement history dynamically.
- Remote Device Control: One-click buttons to instantly Lock, trigger Alarms, request Live Location, and trigger Emergency Mode.
- Heartbeat Monitoring: Dynamically calculates device connectivity, showing a Green "Online" badge if pinged within 5 minutes, or a Red "Offline" badge.
- Instant Install via QR: Dynamically generates QR codes pointing to the local network IP or live Render URL so devices can instantly download the APK.
- Granular Command Logs: Displays the exact lifecycle of a command (Queued, Processing, Executed, Failed) without requiring page refreshes.

=========================================
    ROADMAP / PENDING ISSUES TO SOLVE
=========================================

1. SMS Fallback Edge Cases:
   - Issue: Need to ensure SMS commands still bypass Android 14+ background execution limits when the app is heavily restricted by the OS.
   - Solution: Deeply integrate the Foreground Service (PhoneRakshakService) with the SMS Receiver.

2. Intruder Photo Watermarking:
   - Issue: Photos currently do not have contextual data burned into them.
   - Solution: Add a Canvas watermark to the original image before upload, stamping it with the Timestamp, Location, and Device Info.

3. Stealth Icon / App Disguise:
   - Issue: The app is easily recognizable as "PhoneRakshak" by a thief.
   - Solution: Implement a feature to programmatically change the app icon and name (e.g., to "Calculator" or "Settings") using activity-alias in the AndroidManifest.

4. Multi-Admin 2FA Verification:
   - Issue: The Admin Dashboard currently relies on a single Username/Password.
   - Solution: Implement Time-based One-Time Password (TOTP) or Email OTP to securely log into the Admin panel.

5. Dynamic Theft-Mode Tracking:
   - Issue: Need an active "Theft Mode" that automatically pings location every 10 seconds without manual command triggers, but without draining battery permanently.
   - Solution: Implement a state flag that enables continuous tracking only when 'Theft Mode' is explicitly enabled by the Admin.

